reviews.text: Awesome place to visit. The park is very well maintained, clean grounds and bathrooms, extensive playground for the children and the views of the city are incredible!! This park is huge, and offers plenty of space to relax and enjoy some fresh air!! Lots of good food options on site. We paid 15 LE per person to enter.

More than perfect for a night wedding, wide car parking area, cozy and relaxing place.
The staff were friendly, great place for kids to  play, Good for photosessions.
 It's also good at noon, I've been there several times and will go again.

Beautiful City Macha Allah takes care of its students on the face of who should be distinguished from accommodation to food to entertainment halls and all they need with all this is free of charge. So God rewarded those who are based on it and placed it in the balance of their good deeds

Al-Azhar Park is a public park located in Cairo . Among several honors, this park is listed as one of the world's sixty great public spaces.
The park is a very wide place, it has many posh restaurants, kids area, parking space and memeriesing landscape.
I recommend this place for family outing and  it's a very sutable place for making photo session.

Nice place to get away from the hustle and bustle of the city. Look for telescope area, the highest point overlooking pretty much 360° of that Cairo area. Also various stands for snacks and various restaurants. Price to get in for tourists is 15EP.

What a wonderful day !! Visiting Abdeen Palace is like the historical fantasy which you pass through a very important and precious period of time in the past.
I am lucky to visit this place and look into an amazing details.
Silver museum of king farouk Jewelery and antiques was incredible.
***Unfortunately: The external patio is only available for public and not the rooms and the inner halls as they are within the Republican Presidential Palace.

Artifacts were stunning and it's a well curated and complete collection. I wish there was more English and it was generally explained more thoroughly. The 1 star review is because I am a female tourist and I had an incident with a security gaurd here flirting with me and touching me innappropriatly without permission. I told what seemed to be the head of security who spoke great English and all he said was "okay". I have no idea what action may or may not have been taken but I did not leave comfortable or satisfied. Good job Egypt for living up to your sexist reputation. Way to make tourists feel safe and welcome Abdeen Palace Museum.

Unfortunately the Palace it self is closed to public yet simply visiting the armoury and checking the different pieces is amazing. If you're a gun buff then one day is not enough.
I love the fact that there is a designated parking (if u live in Cairo u will appreciate that)
The garden is a pleasure to walk and roam its grounds
A nice historical building turned into a museum. I wish we could have seen more of the whole palace complex since some of the buildings are not open for visitors as the mosque.
One of the most historical and important palaces in Egypt. Now it's a presidential palace but still we can visit 7 museums that are attached to the Palace.
Best shawarma in Alex. No seating  but some available in next door coffee shop.
High food quality
I loved the place, very delicious food and friendly staff
Food is good. Prices are high
Very nice place to have a meal😊
Situated in the heart of city.Awesome place to hangout with friends. Friends can sit together for long time . Burgers are awesome in taste. All food items are good in taste.
Love to come here, after my coaching classes. It is very nice place for sitting with friends
Well !!!! Who doesn’t know abt Mcdonald 😄❤️ and i think 90% foodies will prefer to take a quick hunger break here. I request those 10% to fill the gap sooner the better 🔥 🔥🔥

It is situated in the Atlantis mall Civil lines......Prayagraj...... 
You all are well aware of the fact that it is a place mostly crowded.... it promotes self service.... the menu is being displayed on the screen above counters.... very limited items are there in this mcD Allahabad...  but it will be freshly prepared and served hot.... drinking water is available for free but one have to ask for it..... its affordable...... one cannot have a cosy atmosphere or a silent atmosphere since its generally over crowded....

I recommend you to taste ice creams...

I would prefer KFC for burgers. But if u want something lite than you ho for it.
The place is always crowded. Try the mcflurry and allu ticki

My Egyptian friend who is local to Cairo told me to check this place out. Well worth the time! Entrance fee for a student at the time was 50£, and they do have a bag check. The additional charge for take photos is also worth doing, AND they do rigorously check to make you paid the photo fee. 

The museum takes about 1-2 hours, and is full of beautiful rugs, coins, door ways and furniture. Most information is in arabic, so its easy to justify the visit for the non-reader museum types. I could hardly understand anything, but still fully enjoyed the look.

For everyone who interested in history, architecture or art, this place is your gem. It has almost everything about the Islamic art. Also it's very organized according to every Islamic era which make it easy to get the history behind it.

The place is amazing. It provides a great experience for Muslim history in different aspects of life. The museum is very clean and neat. The staff is very friendly, there is a small parking slot especially for tourists and there is also a general parking place close to the museum.

This is my favourite museum in Cairo. Solely dedicated to Islamic period, the objects are well displayed. They are chronologically arranged in the gallery towards right. The gallery towards left has objects displayed as per various themes. I was surprised to find items from India (emperor Akbar's time) here. This is a very quiet, clean, not crowded and well maintained museum. Definitely recommend visiting. P. S - need to buy separate ticket for photography even if clicking pictures with phone camera

Very interesting and there were not so many visitors.. There is quite a bit of stuff exhibited there. Nice divisions into the periods. Very interesting weaponry area. Worthy to visit. Photos for extra charge

This beautiful abandoned mansion, which takes up an entire city block in Cairo, has stood empty since 2004. In its heyday, it was one of the most opulent homes in the city – the residence of the Cairo-born Ottoman statesman Said Halim Pasha. But today, it’s a vast, haunting leviathan looming over the surrounding gardens, utterly empty save for the exquisite grand staircase and other grand features.

Said Halim was the grandson of Muhammad Ali, known as the founder of modern Egypt, and would go on to serve as the Grand Vizier of the Ottoman Empire from 1913 to 1917. What’s more, it’s believed that Said Halim’s family would have risen to the top ranks of the Egyptian government
State of neglected art

Look at what have become this precious ancient palace !! 
That was my first school I have ever gone to , and it was so charming , its current miserable condition just because of some legacy issues no less
Worth a look. Check out the Art Nouveau fence.
deserted yes, but try to bribe guard and to get in. it is worth of ...
It was really good. better than Colorado springs McDonald's.. Everything was fresh thank you

The coke machine is always broken, service is crapy, and the wait is not worth the food. You could go somewhere for better food and get it faster. If you are in a rush go somewhere else, this place is not worth it. To top it all off it is not kid friendly anymore. They have electronic devices that don’t even work half the time. I went once and a baby got run over by a high chair. NOT kid friendly at all.
My weakness! Always a crowd but worth the wait. This location one of the cleanest for being so busy.
Wow looks really nice, so modern, good customer service and they have some good deals.

Nasty food..filthy restaurant .. I am so fed up with the sorry excuse for customer service. I came in today and ordered chicken nuggets, no dipping sauce but 2 packs of mayo, they charged me for the mayo, then tried to give me someone elses food. after they handed my food to the car in front of me, they gave me the same food without replacing it. This place is a horrible location. I will never go back to this location. The sad thing is the owners could care less.
We found this great place to eat. After a day of walking and sightseeing we wanted to relax and have a good meal. The food was really good and the cold beer really hit the spot.

The restaurant gives a hut or cottage kind of feel. The ceiling is covered with plants and there are trees inside. They have room heaters to help during winters. The service is average. The food is good and quantity is sufficient for an average eater. The staff is kind too. Must try when in Cairo.
Delicious Egyptian food, many vegan options. The cozy sit-down counterpart to the Felfela Express around the corner. Great for dinner.

Good food at a good price.  But bring cash, they don't take credit card.  There are two restaurant in sane location.  One is for take out or fast order and casual eating, in main street.  Other is for eat in with table sitting, on the side street.

Visited Cairo for one night, this restaurant was recommended by the concierge in our 5* hotel. 
Have to say expected more from a restaurant that says to serve authentic food. Low light and dishes don’t look that appetizing when they arrive, taste... I had a feeling something was missing, and service could definitely be improved, there are so many male servers, but most are standing talking to each other and even when I called on them they would ignore us. 
I wish we had found a better local food restaurant for the only night we were in Egypt.
Very good service for old place, food isn’t great but tasty. They should improve their variety of dishes. Good place to have a beer in quite look historic restaurant
It's very quiet. The crowd is usually polite and lovely. Waiters are friendly. Some dishes are really great.
Well one of the best I have ever been in Cairo I hope for you the best
Classic Egyptian era feel. Some classic swiss dishes available. Alcoholic drinks available. Classy

The place is very cosy with old music such as vaya con dios frank sinatra and bocceli. The food is great especially the swiss cheese fondue which is their signature dish. Awesome place great hospitality and great food and mood.

Old fashioned elegance. Loved it. Only had a drink so can't comment on the food but I would expect it to be good as everything else was. Toilets are clean,  and with soap by the wash basin, had to search for loo roll but it was available.  Will visit again.

We ordered a Pizza on our way to Museum.  Waited for about 15 minutes for our pizza. On the first bite I was about to vomit. I had never had such a bad pizza in my whole life. We paid 105 GL and left without eating it. Noticed that the person before us had also left his/her cake almost untouched. Seems to be a place that rips tourist with garbage service. Never recommend.
A historical place where you can chill and have a good bite. It's cozy, warm and doesn't follow the modern commercial pattern of business. Many highly renowned figures used to and still come here.

Authentic place with lovely ambiance. Known for its good ribs but unfortunately the haven’t any:/ 
Fair prices and fair taste of food
A Cairo icon. Nostalgic. Meeting place for artists, writers, old timers and progressive ideas

Very enjoyable experience. My second time in two years and just as good this time round. Yes, it's in the Ramses Hilton but unless you are destitute or a cheapskate, it is prices are affordable, and it's decent Indian food in Cairo... Thank you, staff and cooks.

BUT TO BE FAIR - While all restaurants charge 12.5% service charge because it is in a hotel the restaurant is obliged to add 14% to the final bill, which does add up surprisingly so.

Not totally my idea of an Indian restaurant, very modern and a bit soul-less, but it is in a 5-star hotel, so I suppose it was to be expected.  The food was average, but beautifully presented. The service was good, but not particularly friendly.  However, considering that it's located in the Ramses Hilton, it wasn't horrendously expensive.  Worth a visit.
Excellent food and service try the lamb rogan josh...mouth watering

Terrible experience. Extremely slow service. They brought us food with chicken in it (we are strict vegetarians) and did not even compensate us for the mistake. Very pricey but expected given the location of the restaurant.
It's one of the Ramses Hilton Restaurant serving Indian style Lunch and Dinner. They have indian chief to prepare food and not an costly to have dinner with friends

This museum is connected to the University - super crowded with students! Our museum guide was very knowledgeable & passionate (I'm told he's a lecturer at the University) about the cultural history of Ethiopia.

Our visit to this museum went smoothly. Our guesthouse host made everything seems seamless!! If you're staying at a guesthouse, take advantage of the service - !!

Provides a rich history and culture of Ethiopia. Itwas a discovery for me to know which community a coffee pot is from by the shape of it. The student guide who accompanied us was very nice in describing the different sections and items if the museum.

The museum itself was great. 100birr per person. However the museum is located within the university, which would have been fine if the guard at the gates didn’t insist on keeping my partner’s ID. Given all we had given him was a driver’s licence. But if we hadn’t brought that along, we would have had to give him a passport. This guard just sits at the gate, not even slightly secure behind a counter, there was no technology to photocopy the ID and he insisted on hanging onto it. I was incredibly unhappy with that and had left a sour taste as we headed in. What was worse was when we decided to let him keep it, we came across a couple foreigners who told us they had taken a cab straight into the University and were not asked to present any ID let alone had to leave it with someone who had no way of securing it. We went back to the guard and demanded our ID back with those foreigners, and he still wouldn’t give it back to us. So, pro tip, if you want to go in, go with a cab, DO NOT walk in unless if you want to risk having your passport taken from you and just left lying around on a chair next to him where anyone could have just taken like we had seen most foreign IDs were when we left.

I would not support the museum for this reason and I urge the university to change their policy. Photocopy the ID if you have to, but foreigners should not be handing in their passport just to enter the university.
Good collection of cultural artifacts. The displays could be better organized and the absence of a good gift shop is a missed opportunity. Worth a visit.
Kind of disappointing but interesting.

After a 10 day road trip around Egypt we spent our last day in Cairo at this hotel. It was bliss. They upgraded us to a suite, which was large, with two bathrooms and a great view. The room service breakfast was delicious and plentiful, and the bed was a pleasure to sleep in. The best part was the spa on the rooftop, with fresh scented aromatic candles burning along the entrance hallway; comfy plush bathrobes and slippers and a hot tub (one for men and one for women). Definitely have a hot drink and sweet at the lobby café. They make amazing chocolate creations, both to eat and to drink.

Staff is unbelievably kind, helpful and devoted. 

I visited most of the 5* hotels in this area (after 2 weeks of being in Cairo) and experienced their lobby, restaurants, pool etc and I can say without a doubt that the Kempinski is the one that gets a 10 on all checkmarks. 

Definitely is my go to hotel in Cairo for my next trips..thank you to the management for doing such a great job with the staff!

Its less than the average 5 Stars regarding the entrance, design and breakfast buffet. The team starting from the security reaching to the rooftop is very kind, helpful and welcoming. Regarding the prices i found it a little bit cheaper comparing to neighbour 5 stars hotels

Rooms are ok although sometimes they smell (smoke) breakfast is good! I originally gave three stars to the hotel but I just upgraded it to 4. Why? Because the staff answered to my comment and very politely promised that they will take better care of the rooms to avoid smoke smell. This is fantastic, well done!

Very enjoyable stay at this hotel, my wife and I booked four nights there and we were pleased with the service and the staff from the reception to the house keeping. 
The buffet is excellent and great variety of food, the service in the breakfast restaurant was excellent, and it is worth mentioning that we have not noticed any of the waiters pushing for tipping.

We come across minor problems with the shower,  one of the managers, a lady by the name of Aya, arranged a quick fix.

In general we were very pleased with the hotel and staff. 

Highly recommended.

This was nice little tower in the middle of Cairo with great views. It may be hard to believe now but for ten years, up to 1971, it was the tallest building in all of Africa. It has a nice little restaurant inside which offers some pastries and coffee if you need a break and perhaps most importantly, even the lobby has air conditioning!

Cairo Tower offers a stunning panoramic view of Cairo and the Pyramids. Telescope view and customized souvenir photographs are available. There is a restaurant and a Cafe with glass view of Cairo. I recommend a visit to this place.

It's only 187 meters high,  not the tallest in the world but tallest in Cairo,  Egypt.. Best time to visit is around sunset so you get to see the day time as well as night lights,  since there is one elevator to and fro, it can get little crowded, prior planning helps,  also check the temperature before going to plan layers of clothing required as it can get chilly towards the evening., I'm not sure how things work in case of elevator breakdown since there is only one elevator to get to the top🤔

One the highest places in Cairo, Egypt from which you can have an enchanted panoramic view of the whole city. It's suitable for enjoying the sunset. It has two restaurants, one them is a 360 degrees rotating restaurant.

The view is awesome, however the crowd makes you anxious. So if you want to make the best of your experience avoid vacations, public holidays, etc. And if you ever find crowded pay extra money which is 75EGYt for the coffee and will not have to wait in the line.
Cheerful place
جاليري للتحف

Really nice place to check out the works of local artists in Cairo. The showcases are always diverse and interesting as they show paintings from multiple artists. Also the gallery almost always has new exhibitions so you'll probably find some new works to ponder upon every time you go there. Recommended for people who enjoy art :)
An art gallery that presents the best artists in a fair price
One of the Olds art gallery in cairo
Fantastic place to see and buy paints
Beautiful art
Very nice gallery space and great exhibitions. Really enjoyed it.
One of the best art galleries in Egypt
Comprehensive, one of the  most organiz Gallery in the town was very  clean professional. They know what they wants.

Although the art halls in Egypt are few but this exhibition is very impressive and the view and arrangement is very good.
I hope to see marketing for this places
Nice setup and very special collections of great artists.
Great pasta but always running out of desserts and they don't serve hot drinks
Good portions, fast service. The Zamalek branch is very tight and gets too crowded though.

I used to be a frequent customer to this restaurant. Last time, I saw one of the staff going to the toilet then back to the kitchen without wakingw his hands ! I advised the manger and requested to ask this staff member to wash his handsh asas this is a basic hygiene practice that staff should be adoptoad. The manger refused to ask him and justified his staff action saying he's only washing dishes ! I advised this was a kitchen area and hygiene standards should be adopted, the manger kept arguing and did nothing ! I wouldn't recommend this restaurant to anyone who's concerned about his/her health
Nice  cosy place    nice meals   friendly staff

Place dirty
Food below average
Staff unprofessional
Need full refurbishment. 
Not recommended

Matching quality of food and beverage with elegance of service and friendliness. A wonderful place to meet friends and/or business partners, amid separate spacious areas for smokers and anti smoking persons. The place has cozy ambience, comfortable seats, very good coffee, savory food, delicious dessert, and great location. Certainly, highly recommended, whether you are a morning, a mid-day, or an evening time person. Many thanks to the staff and the management of Beano's.

Highly recommended specially for breakfast. They have a very good breakfast menu ranging from healthy granola bowls to scrambled eggs to pancakes. The varieties are many, you can find your perfect desire for the breakfast. I’ve ordered crepe with egg, turkey and cheddar. It was very good and the portions are large. I got really full and hardly finished my plate. For drink we tried the frappe with chocolate and it was delicious and large. The serving is nice. The staff are friendly and helpful. 
Overall I enjoyed my visit and recommend it to others. 
The zamalek branch is in perfect location with 2 big floors. Cheers ;)

Cafe is mostly visited by non-arabic speaking guests. The decoration is fantastic. Good reading materials and up to date newspapers and magazines. Good products, well-organized menu and nice view. Noisy cafe (loud voices of staff and loud sounds of handling utensils in the preparation area) with a relatively low level of cleanliness. Some staff are well trained to service standards while others seems not to be.
Good coffee. Wide variety of coffee-based drinks. Tasty food with special breakfast menu. Good, rapid service. Central location. Nice neighborhood.

If you're looking for a continental/American type sandwich shop this will be right up your street. 
Nice sandwiches and coffee as well as delicious cakes.
Smoking upstairs and non smoking downstairs and all reasonably priced.
Thr prices are very good and the quality is excellent. The place is so nice and cozy

Small quiet place..offering deli goods..sandwiches..drinks hot and cold..and limited dessert menue..offers free wifi..good for those who wish to read something or write quietly ..i tried their chocolate cake but didn’t like it much..was dry on top..also hot choclate drink which was good...prices are moderate..has its own crowd ..mostly crave clients go out to have some dessert in this deli.
This is a small coffee shop that serves decent coffee ... they also have light sandwiches and dessert ... nice place for a quick bite and good coffee
Awesome place awesome food.. Awesome everything, a little bit on the expensive side but they employ an amazing staff, and have wonderful service
My fv place in all of zamalek, the staff is really friendly, cozy place, fair prices, good value for money and good for almost everything a cafe/restaurant can offer.

It was a great place,  the atmosphere,  the location,  the service. The total package was so good that makes you happy by the end of the day and think of returning. Alas with the sad news surfacing,  I hope the place makes a come back.
Nice food and location on the Nile

I love this place. It has the perfect view by the Nile especially if you are lucky enough to have a first row table. The food is amazing with a nice set of varieties. It is a suitable place for gatherings and events and in the summer it is advised to go by sunset and in winter the place would be great at noon for a brunch or lunch.
A really beautiful place to spend an evening by the nile

Nice & comfortable friendly place.
And, prices are reasonable relative to the high quality they introduce.
Moreover it has an amazing view for Nile river.

Yummy food and good company are the key ingredients for this place. However, if you're a non-smoker, the combination of cigarette smoke and lack of good ventilation often means you can't stay for too long.
Best place in town.  Great food, super friendly staff....
Amazing atmosphere and those mushrooms were to die for!
Nice place and very good Food and music

It has 2 moods on 2 levels, ground level is dining, drinks and conversation, with proper lighting and low music and limited tables, first floor is darker, more like a pub/bar experience and TV screens for football, whenever important matches are aired with loud speakers and a lot of space. Food is good, but reactively expensive drinks are at reasonable prices though, and service is very good, same waiters have been there for years, and they are extremely efficient and professional. If u are not a regular, you need to reserve in advance. Only draw back is the ventilation system is not good, thus it is too smoky and after a while you cannot take it, when you leave your hair and clothes will stink of smoke.

It was my first time to the place, it is a bit tricky to get there are it is inside a building on the 1st floor, but once there, you will find everything well set, not that fancy. I was looking for a light vegan meal, so I went for the vegetable spring rolls and the glass noddles soup, both were very nice, it toke a bit of time to get the plates but it was hot and well served. Prices are a bit higher than expected for portions but accepted. Will go back to try out other plates.

I know it is challenging to run a resto business, especially if it serves fish, which need to be fresh and freshly cooked. Same with other dishes - be it poultry or meats or even veggies. But that is what customers look and pay for. Thai cuisine is famous for the use of freshest ingredients that are often stir fried or steamed - cooking methods that relies so much on how fresh the ingredients are. I hope Sabai Sabai continues to improve on this. I am a real fan and would encourage others to try this. Perhaps a steady flow of diners would help ensure good turnover of fresh ingredients.

A delightful place for Asian (especially Thai & Malay) cuisine tasting & experience. They offer ample variety choices of food, desserts & drinks here. The dishes are very delicious, well presented and mostly accurate with the original taste from the origin nations. Very satisfying if you’re an Asian/someone with passion for the Asian taste.

The place is very nice & comfortable to enjoy your meal. The location is exact as in the Google Maps, but the restaurant entrance can be a bit confusing to look for, do ask people around if you’re lost.
The entrance of the building complex is not that welcoming. Authentic Thai food and jasmine rice are so good. Thai beer as well as Egyptian beer served here! Friendly. Great service.

It used to be my favorite Thai place but the quality has gone down a lot lately, to the extent that I won’t be eating there again, UNLESS I hear of some major quality improvement.

The curry in all the dishes I have had lately has been very diluted: watery consistence and very limited flavor. Also the ingredients (seasoning and vegetables) have just been LESS in terms of diversity and quantity.

I had a duck curry, which came out super fatty and the sauce was dominated by a strong odor that was on the fishy side. If anyone with a basic sense of smell and no culinary experience had smelled THAT, they would have flushed it down the toilet, not offered it to customers.

Sabai SabIai used to be my foolproof recommendation to friends in Zamalek and the surrounding areas, it will go back to being so if you significantly improve quality AND consistency.

So good luck.
Thr prices are very good and the quality is excellent. The place is so nice and cozy

This is a small coffee shop that serves decent coffee ... they also have light sandwiches and dessert ... nice place for a quick bite and good coffee
Awesome place awesome food.. Awesome everything, a little bit on the expensive side but they employ an amazing staff, and have wonderful service
My fv place in all of zamalek, the staff is really friendly, cozy place, fair prices, good value for money and good for almost everything a cafe/restaurant can offer.

Nice restaurant with good view of Old Town. Food was great, though the bottom sides of my fish fillets on the fish & chips were slightly soggy compared to the nice crispy top sides. Still good nonetheless. Also ordered the peel & eat shrimp as an appetizer. Nice big pieces of shrimp cooked perfectly. I could do with a little less of the buttery sauce that it sits in though. All in all, good food, good service - I'll be back.

So being from the Midwest we are not able to get fresh seafood usually. So when on one of the coasts, seafood is a must! Ordered the Fisherman’s platter, which had fish, shrimp and scallops with fries. All were good, but I felt the scallops were the best I’ve ever had! Not rubbery, very soft and tasty. Sad there were only two on the plate! All in all, this would have been a 5-star, except I felt the portion size was less than the price should have suggested.

Nice restaurant in Old Town. Good selection of dishes, service was friendly but nothing wowed me.  I would be happy to eat here again as I enjoyed the food but felt it could have been better executed.  I had the fish tacos and while the fish portion was very generous the other accompaniments felt a little overwhelmed.  It is a fish market so maybe it's just me?
The food was fresh and tasty. I had a big plate of mixed seafood. The crab cake and the grilled veggies was yummy. Atmosphere was nice and busy. Great selection of beers.

So disappointed with my small Captains plate for $26.00!!! I got two shrimp, one oyster, one scallop and a fish fillet.  I used to share the small platter!!! What happened???? I told the server that he should let customers know how small the portion is now!!!  The flavor was good and the rest of my party enjoyed their lobsters and Cobb salad or I would have rated it a 1.  This has always been one of our favorite places to bring out of town guests.

It was a great place,  the atmosphere,  the location,  the service. The total package was so good that makes you happy by the end of the day and think of returning. Alas with the sad news surfacing,  I hope the place makes a come back.
Nice food and location on the Nile

I love this place. It has the perfect view by the Nile especially if you are lucky enough to have a first row table. The food is amazing with a nice set of varieties. It is a suitable place for gatherings and events and in the summer it is advised to go by sunset and in winter the place would be great at noon for a brunch or lunch.
A really beautiful place to spend an evening by the nile

Nice & comfortable friendly place.
And, prices are reasonable relative to the high quality they introduce.
Moreover it has an amazing view for Nile river.
If you like the smell of history and wonder about grandparents' living you will sure love this place
Good atmosphere ..... but the last I checked this place most of the rooms were closed

The house of Suhaimi is a beautiful example of the ancient Islamic heritage. 
The only problem was that most of the house’s corridors were closed, and the show was limited to a small area.
I was impressed by the region as a whole.
Beautiful Historic Islamic Place . Recommended to Visit As A Part Of ElMoez St. Visit.

The ticket is 10 EGP for Egyptians, 80 for foreigners.

A tour there would take about one hour or one hour and a half.

A old big house with wide rooms and a few old remnants and Arabic and Islamic decorations everywhere, and some parts are closed, however if you don't have a guide or some expert who can explain to you what you're seeing and enhance your experience with relevant historical stories, I would think it might be a little bit boring!

One of the main attractions that you should visit when touring Cairo. The mosque is in Khan Al Khalilli and this is a historical site that you must do and enjoy touring. Al Fishawi Cafe is there and you can spend good time enjoying the local culture while having a coffee or tea. You should not miss out on this.  Go there in the evening, the best time. It is safe.
A must visit, If you come to Cairo. Wonderful architecture. Strongly recommended.
Magnificent mosque. Good amenities inside. Very convenient for prayers.
Fantastic mosque! Would recommend to all my brothers! Allahu Akbar!
Can’t describe my feelings when I walk in this place I just feel so relieved, setting on a coffee shop in that place can really make your day.
An ancient Egyptian architectural wonder .... a must see when you are in Cairo ...still the structure is intact and I think it would withstand any odds for ages to come...

huge historical mosque, built by the mother of an Egyptian gouverner, very well decorated from inside and outside, the engineers did their best for more than 20 years to finish this big architecture and to look as big as it's neighbour historical unique mosque of sultan hassan.
Beautiful mosque and houses the graves of the royal family from Khedive Ismaiel and onwards

Mohammad Reza Shah Pahlavi
Iran's king . After the October 1978 rebellion,Mohammad Reza died from complications of Waldenström's macroglobulinemia on 27 July 1980, aged 60. Egyptian President Sadat gave the Shah a state funeral. In addition to members of the Pahlavi family, Anwar Sadat, Richard Nixon and Constantine II of Greece attended the funeral ceremony in Cairo.

Mohammad Reza is buried in the Al Rifa'i Mosque in Cairo, a mosque of great symbolic importance. Also buried there is Farouk of Egypt, Mohammad Reza's former brother-in-law. The tombs lie to the left of the entrance. Years earlier, his father and predecessor, Reza Shah had also initially been buried at the Al Rifa'i Mosque.
One of the oldest mosques in Cairo. Beautiful architectural beauty of this place will touch your soul for sure.

An amazing place, with historical furniture and an artistic sense. Simple , yet royal.
The guide was of a great help to get good information.
Definitely go, and take your kids along.
Proud to have such a place to visit
There is a lot of history to see and hear about, it is a peaceful place gives you a lot of satisfaction. Words can't describe it it is just beautiful

This is a great museum and there are a lot of things you can see this museum. Even though you would be tired from visiting the next door Ibn Tulun Mosque I would highly recommend seeing this place. You can do it at your own pace and there are many rooms in this museum to see and each have their unique things to see. If you have the Cairo pass then you don't pay the entry fee but you will have to pay to take photos. If our dont want to pay for the photo pass just don't take photos at the ground level and the levels above are fine. There are museum care takers who will show and explain the different rooms and best to pay them a little token upfront. James Bond's Spy Who Loved Me was shot in one of the terraces. There is also a secret hidden room which is impossible to find unless the caretakers show it to you.

Please don't miss and go at your own pace, and there are stairs to climb to visit each room.

One of my favourite places in Cairo, such a hidden gem! It is an oasis of serenity in this megalopolis chaos!

Apparently the guided visit is short, so DYI !

I love the architecture, the artifacts, the garden and the book/gifts shop. The " tales of the kritlia" book is great! The house had been associated to some interesting fairy tales:)
Very cool museum. Something off the trail of the ancient... and into the modern age of Egypt. Which is arguably more interesting.

Most underrated place in all of Egypt. Accessibility can be tricky but it's totally worth it. It's the biggest church in the middle East carved into a mountain. And don't forget to see the graffiti from the first floor of the services building. Also if you go during the day, there's zip lining and on specific days of the week, there's tattooing. Here's a picture of the auditorium. #CaveArchitecture

This place is insane. I think it is amazing but it's certainly not for everyone. The church is impressive to say the least but, to get there, you have to go through Garbage City. It is exactly as the name suggests.. a city of garbage where the residents collect, sort, and sell it. Certainly not for everyone, but it is interesting to say the least.
Absolutely beautiful place. REGARDLESS of your religious affiliation, it's a spiritual experience.

A very different place in a huge rock formation in the Southwest side of Cairo. An ampitheater-like architecture with some beautiful stonework. Even the trip to go there is an experience passing through some really poor areas of Old Cairo.
Wow! I serve an amazing, creative God.
They had a great selection of middle eastern fare, well made, and open buffet style dining in an intimate atmosphere. Our waiter was so kind and delivered great service to us.
Zitouni is nice resturant and environment. Few items provided , food presentation is moderate . Taste is fine . No variety in dessert
Excellent food quality, the staff are extremely friendly. Slightly overpriced for such kind of food. But really worth a visit.
Very pricey but it's worth it. The brunch is nothing but amazing. The staffs are very warm and welcoming.
Best Fine Dining in Cairo. Best Quality, service and Manager
